---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import InstitutionalBio from '../../components/InstitutionalBio.astro';
import RelatedResearch from '../../components/RelatedResearch.astro';
import ChartSaasCategoryChange from '../../components/charts/ChartSaasCategoryChange.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Welcome to the SaaSpocalypse",
  "description": "Software that can be vibe-coded by a small team has lost all pricing power, while AI-resistant SaaS categories raised entry-tier prices up to three times faster than inflation. Six years of pricing data across 65 tools and 12 categories.",
  "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com/resources/saas-pricing-inflation",
  "image": "https://ranking-atlas.com/assets/images/resources/saas-pricing-inflation/hero.jpg",
  "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Daniel Grainger", "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com/about" },
  "datePublished": "2026-04-13T00:00:00+00:00",
  "dateModified": "2026-05-14T00:00:00+00:00",
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Ranking Atlas", "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com" }
};
---

<Layout
  title="Welcome to the SaaSpocalypse | Ranking Atlas"
  description="Software that can be vibe-coded by a small team has lost all pricing power, while AI-resistant SaaS categories raised entry-tier prices up to three times faster than inflation."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />
  <script is:inline src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/4.4.1/chart.umd.js"></script>

<div class="bg-white">

  <!-- ── 1. Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="pt-20 md:pt-28 pb-16 border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-brand font-medium mb-3 text-center">Data Report</div>
      <h1 class="font-serif font-medium text-[1.75rem] md:text-[2rem] lg:text-[2.25rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-[1.15] mb-3 text-center">
        Welcome to the SaaSpocalypse
      </h1>
      <p class="font-serif italic text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[1.55] text-body mt-2 mb-8">
        Software that can be vibe-coded by a small team has lost all pricing power, while AI-resistant SaaS categories raised entry-tier prices up to three times faster than inflation.
      </p>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <ChartSaasCategoryChange />
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[#FBFAF7] border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 rounded-2xl p-5 mb-6">
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Content Written By:</p>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Daniel Grainger</p>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Founder, Ranking Atlas</p>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-[#64748B]">Published April 2026</p>
      </div>

      <nav class="bg-[#FBFAF7] border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 rounded-2xl p-5" aria-label="Article sections">
        <p class="text-[14px] font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Navigation</p>
        <ul class="flex flex-col space-y-2 text-[14px]">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#overview" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Overview</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#key-takeaways" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Key Takeaways</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#category-medians" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">AI-Resistant Categories Raised Prices Above Inflation</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#largest-increases" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Kayako Raised Entry-Tier Prices by 427% in Six Years</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#largest-cuts" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">AI-Replicable Tools Cut Entry-Tier Prices by Up to 64%</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#snapshots" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Two Pricing Trajectories Verified Against the Wayback Machine</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#full-dataset" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">All 65 Tools Ranked by Price Change</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#methodology" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Methodology</a></li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5"><span aria-hidden="true" class="inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#0A0F1E]/30 shrink-0"></span><a href="#limitations" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark hover:underline underline-offset-2">Limitations</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 2. Overview ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="overview" class="py-16 border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">Overview</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7]">
        <p>The SaaSpocalypse has a clear pattern. Software categories whose core function can now be approximated by a small team with AI coding assistants have lost all pricing power. Visual Design fell 38.9%. CRM, Productivity, and Dev tooling all returned median price changes of exactly 0.0%. Project Management came in at +2.0%. Meanwhile, AI-resistant categories raised entry-tier prices well above inflation: Analytics up 81.3%, HR up 66.7%, Marketing up 57.9%, Accounting up 53.3%, Support up 50.0%. Against a 27.1% US CPI rise over the same six years, the gap between vibe-codeable and AI-proof SaaS is the widest in the industry's history.</p>
        <p>Ranking Atlas pulled the lowest-priced monthly subscription from 65 SaaS vendor pricing pages in January 2020, then repeated the exercise in April 2026. 2020 prices were verified against the closest available <a href="https://web.archive.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark underline underline-offset-2">Wayback Machine</a> snapshot for each tool. 2026 prices were taken from live pricing pages captured in the same month. The US Consumer Price Index rose 27.1% over the same period (BLS, all urban consumers), giving a clean reference line for what counts as a real-terms price increase.</p>
        <p>The pattern is consistent across the dataset. Tools whose core function can be replicated by a small team using current AI coding assistants and generative tools have no pricing power left. Tools that require human process, regulated reporting, or integrations AI cannot yet replicate are raising prices roughly three times faster than inflation. The most extreme cases sit at the edges: Kayako, a support tool, raised its entry tier 427% in six years. Vtiger CRM cut its entry tier by 64.3% over the same period.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 3. Key Takeaways ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="key-takeaways" class="py-16 bg-[#FBFAF7] border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7]">
        <li><strong>Analytics raised median entry-tier prices by 81.3%, three times the rate of inflation.</strong> HR (+66.7%), Marketing (+57.9%), Accounting (+53.3%), and Support (+50.0%) all sit well above the 27.1% US CPI benchmark. These are categories whose core work depends on human process, regulated reporting, or integrations that current AI tooling cannot reliably replicate.</li>
        <li><strong>CRM, Productivity, and Dev tooling all returned median price changes of 0.0%.</strong> Project Management came in at +2.0%, well below inflation. Visual Design fell 38.9% on a small sample of two tools. Every category at or below the inflation line is one whose entry-tier function can now be approximated by a small team with AI assistants.</li>
        <li><strong>Kayako, a customer support tool, raised its entry tier from $15 to $79 per agent per month, a 427% increase.</strong> Klipfolio (Analytics, +185.7%), JazzHR (HR, +182.1%), Later (Marketing, +177.8%), and Hiver (Support, +150%) round out the top five. Every tool that raised prices more than 150% sits in an AI-resistant category.</li>
        <li><strong>Vtiger CRM cut its entry tier from $42 to $15 per user per month, a 64.3% decline.</strong> Venngage (Visual Design, -61.2%), Copper (CRM, -50%), CircleCI (Dev, -50%), and Constant Contact (Marketing, -40%) make up the rest of the top five cuts. Four of the five sit in AI-replicable categories.</li>
        <li><strong>Asana's Premium tier (now Starter) has held at $10.99 per user per month since January 2020.</strong> Holding flat against 27.1% CPI is itself a real-terms price cut of roughly 21%. The flat-list-price defence is the most common move in AI-exposed categories.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 4. Finding 1: Category medians ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="category-medians" class="py-16 border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[1.5rem] tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-6">AI-Resistant Categories Raised Prices Above Inflation</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-body text-[15px] leading-[1.7] mb-8">
        <p>Median percentage change in lowest monthly entry tier by category, sorted by magnitude of change. All categories include at least three tools except Visual Design (n=2), disclosed below. The 27.1% line is US CPI over the same period.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#0A0F1E]/8 bg-[#FBFAF7]">
